  <Interfaces />
  <Docs>
    <summary>When implemented by an object, indicates that the object is capable of being used with the <see cref="T:GameStack.Graphics.Batch" /> class to batch draw calls.</summary>
    <remarks>Any object implementing IBatchable has an additional responsibility: when the object is asked to draw itself, it must check if there is a <see cref="T:GameStack.Graphics.Batch" /> is in scope using the <see cref="M:GameStack.Graphics.ScopedObject.Find{T}" /> method. If there is, it must call <see cref="M:GameStack.Graphics.Batch.Draw(GameStack.Graphics.IBatchable)" /> instead of drawing itself normally.</remarks>
  </Docs>
